@ A single slug-like alien inadvertently slides into the hydroponics bay. It pauses, its many eyes seemingly entranced by the lush, vibrant flora. 


@ Slowly, it glides towards a large pot containing a thriving fern. With a soft, squelching sound, it begins to burrow into the rich soil, disappearing beneath the surface.

@note: If I hadn't seen them rip a man apart before, I could have sworn it was harmless and kind of cute.

